1365
02:00:14.010 --> 02:00:18.175
'Photographs show the river below the dam
in full flood.


1366
02:00:18.302 --> 02:00:21.420
'The attacks were pressed home
from a very low level


1367
02:00:21.552 --> 02:00:26.422
'with great determination and coolness
in the face of fierce resistance.


1368
02:00:26.552 --> 02:00:29.875
'Eight of the Lancasters are missing.'

1369
02:01:45.135 --> 02:01:47.127
Is it true?
All those fellows lost?


1370
02:01:47.260 --> 02:01:49.673
Only two aircrafts went down
in the attacks.


1371
02:01:49.802 --> 02:01:52.135
That was Hopgood's over the MÃ¶hne
and Maudslay's over the Eder.


1372
02:01:52.260 --> 02:01:54.593
Astell got it soon after crossing the coast,

1373
02:01:54.718 --> 02:01:58.382
and Dinghy Young was shot down
over the sea on his way home.


1374
02:01:59.343 --> 02:02:01.130
The rest we don't know about.

1375
02:02:01.260 --> 02:02:03.718
They've been calling them since midnight,
but they haven't answered.


1376
02:02:04.510 --> 02:02:07.344
The flak was bad,
worse than I expected.


1377
02:02:08.468 --> 02:02:10.255
56 men!

1378
02:02:11.052 --> 02:02:15.001
If I'd known it was going to be like this,
I'd never have started it.


1379
02:02:15.885 --> 02:02:17.296
You mustn't think that way.

1380
02:02:17.427 --> 02:02:19.510
If these fellows had known
they wouldn't be coming back,


1381
02:02:19.635 --> 02:02:21.001
they'd have gone just the same.

1382
02:02:21.135 --> 02:02:23.297
There isn't a single one of them
that would have dropped out.


1383
02:02:23.427 --> 02:02:25.635
I knew them all,
I know that's true.


1384
02:02:27.427 --> 02:02:29.885
Look, you've had a worse night
than any of us.


1385
02:02:30.010 --> 02:02:33.208
Why don't you go and find a doctor
and ask for one of his sleeping pills?


1386
02:02:34.760 --> 02:02:36.877
Aren't you going to turn in, Gibby?

1387
02:02:37.010 --> 02:02:40.048
No, I... I have
to write some letters first.